snippet.textDisplay: Putting cloning into a story is like putting time travel into a story.  Maybe you can pull it off, but for every problem you solve with it you usually wind up creating 10 more problems.  The MCU was only able to pull off time travel because they essentially told audiences "don't think about it too much," and they had built up enough goodwill that the viewers indulged them.  Disney Star Wars has none of that goodwill and it's obvious to all that they completely mangled the story.  They were desperate to come up with a plot for TROS so they brought back Palpatine.  Now they're desperate to retcon an explanation for that since none was included in the movie.  It's a complete crap show and they're probably better off pretending the whole sequel trilogy never happened.

snippet.textDisplay:
None of it works. If Senator Palpatine was a clone of young Sidious, why is the original disfigured? That happened in the prequels, remember? As Rich so astutely pointed out, the version of Sidious in Rise of Skywalker had burned up fingers and looked like he'd been thrown down a Death Star Throne Room shaft and exploded.


We've seen what Star Wars cloning looks like with the Clone Troopers. They are grown from embryos, so a clone wouldn't have the exact same damage we've seen Sidous take. Can you even clone midichlorians? How else could clones use space magic? The whole idea falls apart, which is proof that this is just Lucasfilm trying to say they didn't green light Palpatine's return just because they needed a big bad guy last minute and there's nobody at Disney interested in making sure all this garbage makes sense.


Mickey Daddy needs to send them to their room for while to make TV Shows... no more movies until they've had time to think about what they did wrong and promise not to do that anymore.
